bug.short_desc: [PATCH] (totem-nautilus) The Audio/Video pane in nautilus' Properties dialog truncates data
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1233035 Screenshots: before/after (broken/patched) comparison of Properties dialogs for OGV, WAV, MP3.
Description of problem: As noted @ gnome bugzilla, "Multimedia tags are ellipsized too drastically" in the Nautilus Properties dialog, including Fedora 25's current updates disting build. A screenshot composite is attached comparing the Properties panes for OGV, WAV, and MP3 media files, with the left-hand ("before") images taken from the current F25 Nautilus.
A Gnome BZ commenter pointed out that this was due to the "Properties page width is too small" bug filed against totem (linked here as the upstream External Bug), for which patches are available in the upstream bugzilla, but not yet committed.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): totem-nautilus-1:3.22.0-1.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: Always, when viewing Properties for any of the > 100 MIME types supported by libtotem-properties
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Navigate to a location containing a multimedia file in Nautilus 2. Select the file, choose "Properties" from the context menu or type Ctrl+i. 3. Select the "Audio/Video" pane
Actual results: Metadata is displayed in an extremely narrow section of the window, with most of the detail unreadable. (See attached screenshot "before" photos.)
Expected results: Metadata is formatted to the full width of the Properties dialog, and all of the information is readable. (See attached screenshot "After" photos.)
Additional info: Because the patches were already available in Gnome bugzilla to fix this issue, I combined and rebased them to apply cleanly to the sources from F25's current totem-3.22.0-1.fc25.src.rpm, and built a patched set of RPMs containing the fixes. After installing those RPMs and restarting nautilus, I was able to capture the right-hand ("after") screenshots in the attached image, showing the problem fixed.
It'd be great if we could get a set of totem packages built and pushed to update with this patch included, because without it the Audio/Video Properties pane is completely useless.

Created attachment 1233036 Patches from Gnome BZ, combined and rebased to F25 updates totem sources
Here's the necessary patch, rebased to apply cleanly on F25-updates' current totem-3.22.0-1.fc25 source tree. This patchfile combines all of the relevant patches from the Gnome bug (attachments 341339, 341340, 341341, 341342, 341483, 341484, and 341485).
The only totem source file modified by the patch is data/properties.ui
The patches in question have now been committed upstream (see upstream bug @ Gnome Desktop 771653), so we'll also get them for free when Totem makes its next point release.
Indeed it has, closing as fixed in stable updates.
